explanation.en:
This patient has had several days of poor oral intake and diarrhea and now has signs of hypovolemia (eg, dry mucous membranes, sunken eyes) and shock (eg, lethargy, severe hypotension). With shock, there is poor organ and tissue perfusion that leads to tissue hypoxia with increased anaerobic metabolism and consequent lactic acidosis. In response to the reduction in pH caused by metabolic acidosis there is increased ventilation to increase CO2 exhalation (ie, compensatory respiratory alkalosis). {{exhibit_1}}

Severe diarrhea causes loss of bicarbonate in the stool, further contributing to metabolic acidosis and a compensatory increase in ventilation in this patient.

(Choices A, B, and E) The reduced cardiac output in hypovolemic shock stimulates arteriolar vasoconstriction to increase systemic vascular resistance and help increase blood pressure. This reduces arteriolar capacitance. There is also contraction of venous smooth muscle to cause venular constriction and help increase venous return to the heart. The constricted vasculature reduces extravasation of intravascular fluid. In contrast, septic shock involves peripheral vasodilation with relaxation of vascular smooth muscle, increased vascular capacitance, and extravasation of intravascular fluid.

(Choice C) Blood volume is markedly decreased in hypovolemic shock, leading to decreased central venous pressure. Central venous pressure is increased in cardiogenic shock and obstructive shock. {{exhibit_2}}

Educational objective:
Hypovolemic shock results from markedly decreased blood volume, which reduces central venous pressure and cardiac output and leads to increased systemic vascular resistance (peripheral vasoconstriction). Shock causes reduced organ and tissue perfusion, which leads to lactic acidosis (metabolic acidosis) and a compensatory increase in ventilation (ie, compensatory respiratory alkalosis). {{exhibit_3}} {{exhibit_4}} {{exhibit_5}} {{exhibit_6}}

explanation.zh:
该患者有数天进食不良和腹泻的病史，现在出现血容量不足的体征（如，粘膜干燥，眼睛凹陷）和休克（如，嗜睡，严重低血压）。休克时，器官和组织灌注不良，导致组织缺氧，无氧代谢增加，从而导致乳酸性酸中毒。为了应对代谢性酸中毒引起的 pH 值降低，通气增加以增加 CO2 呼出（即，代偿性呼吸性碱中毒）。{{exhibit_1}}

严重的腹泻会导致粪便中碳酸氢盐的流失，这进一步导致代谢性酸中毒，并导致该患者通气增加以进行代偿。

（选项 A、B 和 E）在低血容量性休克中，心输出量减少会刺激小动脉血管收缩，以增加体循环血管阻力，有助于增加血压。这降低了小动脉容量。静脉平滑肌也会收缩，导致小静脉收缩，有助于增加静脉回流到心脏。血管收缩减少了血管内液体的外渗。相比之下，感染性休克涉及周围血管舒张，伴有血管平滑肌松弛、血管容量增加和血管内液体外渗。

（选项 C）在低血容量性休克中，血容量显著减少，导致中心静脉压降低。心源性休克和梗阻性休克时，中心静脉压升高。{{exhibit_2}}

教育目标：
低血容量性休克是由于血容量显著减少，导致中心静脉压和心输出量降低，并导致体循环血管阻力（周围血管收缩）增加。休克会导致器官和组织灌注减少，从而导致乳酸性酸中毒（代谢性酸中毒）和通气增加以进行代偿（即，代偿性呼吸性碱中毒）。{{exhibit_3}} {{exhibit_4}} {{exhibit_5}} {{exhibit_6}}
